*   ## **_WWE WOMEN'S WORLD CHAMPIONSHIP: LIV MORGAN(c) DEF. RHEA RIPLEY_**
    

DOMINIK MYSTERIO HAS TURNED ON RHEA RIPLEY

LIV MORGAN RETAINS THE WWE WOMEN'S WORLD CHAMPIONSHIP THANKS TO A DISTRACTION FROM DOMINIK!!

AFTER THE MATCH DOMINIK PICKS UP LIV AND THE MAKE OUT!!

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/2f9c4342-52da-4a70-ab3f-65ae40415836/Messenger_creation_ae163800-3931-42bb-8bb9-c3a8881ccb25.jpeg)

* * *

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/7ed9dd05-8017-493f-8c04-c0555f18c676/20240803_164001.jpg)

Damien Priest is FURIOUS at what Dom has done. He busts into the Judgement Day clubhouse and questioned if any of them knew Dom was going to betray Rhea.

He takes it too far with Finn Balor and Balor tells him to calm down. They're gonna go look for Dom.

* * *

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/93d47bda-3f09-46fd-9fd8-72ab784ff7f7/20240803_165029.jpg)

*   ## **_INTERCONTINENTAL CHAMPIONSHIP: BRON BREAKER DEF. SAMI ZAYN(c)_**
    

Fast paced action. The Bron Breakker era has arrived.

* * *

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/11c9807f-1877-46ab-b700-dde88a7bc384/20240803_172105.jpg)

UNITED STATES CHAMPIONSHIP: LA KNIGHT DEF. LOGAN PAUL(c)

Logan Paul brought MGK out with him and that led to MGK eventually giving Logan a pair of Brass Knuckles.

But LA Knight’s skull is made of steel and he powers his way through to a victory.

* * *

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/91a45624-65e8-4f6e-ba69-fb7e61549526/20240803_174813.jpg)

*   ## **_WWE WOMEN'S CHAMPIONSHIP: NIA JAX DEF. BAYLEY(c)_**
    

BAYLEY kicked out of a Bonzai Drop and even POWERBOMBS Nia Jax at one point. But Tiffany Stratton tries to cash in and this distraction allows Nia Jax to win the Women's Championship from BAYLEY.

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/af6bfd9f-3689-45ae-af32-233eaedebba4/20240803_174820.jpg)

* * *

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/1baa7aa9-854a-4f09-834e-8f3bca0a72bc/20240803_182429.jpg)

*   ## **_DREW MCINTYRE DEF. CM PUNK_**
    

Seth Rollins allows them to do what they want to each other until he finally begins to get involved.

At one point, Rollins is knocked out of the ring when Punk is pinning Drew. Punk blames Rollins for not counting to 3.

CM Punk is able to get his bracelet back from Drew. But he loses it and Rollins puts it on to keep safe.

Punk sees Rollins wearing it. They argue. He hits Rollins with GTS.

Drew low blows Punk, hits the Claymore, gets the pinfall and takes his bracelet back.

* * *

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/ba7dc89d-0c12-4733-8185-061832c0271b/20240803_185708.jpg)

*   ## **_WWE WORLD HEAVYWEIGHT CHAMPIONSHIP: GUNTHER def. DAMIEN PRIEST(c)_**
    

Gunther beats on Damien for most of the match but Priest gets some great shots in, including one that busts open Gunther's chest.

It looks like Damien Priest has Gunther beaten when Balor puts Gunther’s foot on the ropes.

FINN BALOR HAS TURNED ON DAMIEN PRIEST AND COST HIM THE WORLD CHAMPIONSHIP.

GUNTHER IS THE WWE WORLD HEAVYWEIGHT CHAMPION

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/dd67f931-940b-4494-863e-3d22b44e58bc/20240803_185810.jpg)

